<p>
<seg id=1> Notwithstanding the fighting between Serbian security force and Albanian separatist in the past few days, international supervision personnel in Kosovo still hope that a cease-fire can be re-instated. </seg>
<seg id=2> On Monday in Prishtina, a spokesman of the supervision personnel said that the situation is calm in the province of Kosovo, Yugoslavia. </seg>
<seg id=3> The fighting last week killed at least 12. </seg>
<seg id=4> The chairman of Organization for Security and Co-operation in Europe, Geremek (Polish), condemned both sides to the fighting for causing the violent conflict. </seg>
</p>
